<title>USA: Shareholders OK Allegro-Software Publishing merger.</title>
<headline>Shareholders OK Allegro-Software Publishing merger.</headline>
<dateline>FAIRFIELD, N.J. 1996-12-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Allegro New Media Inc and Software Publishing Corp said their shareholders voted to approve the merger of Software with a wholly owned subsidiary of Allegro.</p>
<p>The merger is expected to become effective on December 27.</p>
<p>Each share of Softweare common will be converted into 0.26805 share of Allegro.</p>
<p>Allegro is expected to be listed under the symbol SPCO on the Nasdaq Small-Cap market.</p>
